{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"cat <<'EOF' > harness/checklist.md\n# MiniLang LSP Harness Checklist\n\n1. \"'`encodeMessage` must return a valid JSON-RPC framed payload where every response starts with `Content-Length: <byteLength>`, followed by `'\"\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n\"'`, and the JSON body equals `JSON.stringify(message)`.\n2. `MessageBuffer.push` must accept fragmented input and return `[]` for incomplete frames, then return exactly each fully reconstructed message object in order once enough bytes arrive.\n3. `MessageBuffer.push` must decode multiple concatenated frames from streamed input and emit all complete messages in sequence.\n4. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'initialize'})\"'` must return `jsonrpc: '\"'2.0'\"'`, the same `id`, and capabilities containing `textDocumentSync`, `completionProvider`, `definitionProvider`, and `hoverProvider`.\n5. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'shutdown'})\"'` must return `{jsonrpc: '\"'2.0', id, result: null}\"'` and `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'exit'})\"'` must return `null` without throwing.\n6. On `didOpen`, the server must publish diagnostics for both undefined symbol references and function arity mismatches and also store those diagnostics in `getDiagnostics(uri)`.\n7. On malformed input such as brace/syntax errors, parsing must still recover and still publish semantic diagnostics it can compute (including undefined and arity issues when present).\n8. On `didChange`, document content must be updated incrementally and published diagnostics must replace the previous set for that URI (old diagnostics that no longer apply are removed).\n9. Completion responses must only include items matching the current token prefix at cursor position, and must include symbols available in the current scope (not leaking symbols outside scope).\n10. Completion items must expose function signature information for function symbols (for example parameter list in `label`/`detail`/`insertText`).\n11. Go-to-definition must resolve symbol declarations, and when a name exists both locally and elsewhere, it must choose the local-scope declaration.\n12. Hover must return symbol/function documentation text for the symbol at cursor and include function signature text for function symbols.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"cat <<'EOF' > harness/checklist.md\n# MiniLang LSP Harness Checklist\n\n1. \"'`encodeMessage` must return a valid JSON-RPC framed payload where every response starts with `Content-Length: <byteLength>`, followed by `'\"\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n\"'`, and the JSON body equals `JSON.stringify(message)`.\n2. `MessageBuffer.push` must accept fragmented input and return `[]` for incomplete frames, then return exactly each fully reconstructed message object in order once enough bytes arrive.\n3. `MessageBuffer.push` must decode multiple concatenated frames from streamed input and emit all complete messages in sequence.\n4. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'initialize'})\"'` must return `jsonrpc: '\"'2.0'\"'`, the same `id`, and capabilities containing `textDocumentSync`, `completionProvider`, `definitionProvider`, and `hoverProvider`.\n5. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'shutdown'})\"'` must return `{jsonrpc: '\"'2.0', id, result: null}\"'` and `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'\"'exit'})\"'` must return `null` without throwing.\n6. On `didOpen`, the server must publish diagnostics for both undefined symbol references and function arity mismatches and also store those diagnostics in `getDiagnostics(uri)`.\n7. On malformed input such as brace/syntax errors, parsing must still recover and still publish semantic diagnostics it can compute (including undefined and arity issues when present).\n8. On `didChange`, document content must be updated incrementally and published diagnostics must replace the previous set for that URI (old diagnostics that no longer apply are removed).\n9. Completion responses must only include items matching the current token prefix at cursor position, and must include symbols available in the current scope (not leaking symbols outside scope).\n10. Completion items must expose function signature information for function symbols (for example parameter list in `label`/`detail`/`insertText`).\n11. Go-to-definition must resolve symbol declarations, and when a name exists both locally and elsewhere, it must choose the local-scope declaration.\n12. Hover must return symbol/function documentation text for the symbol at cursor and include function signature text for function symbols.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"cat <<'EOF' > harness/selftest.mjs\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport encodeMessage, { MessageBuffer, MiniLangServer } from '../src/server.mjs';\n\nconst request = (method, params = {}, id = 1) => ({\n  jsonrpc: '2.0',\n  id,\n  method,\n  params,\n});\n\nconst notification = (method, params = {}) => ({\n  jsonrpc: '2.0',\n  method,\n  params,\n});\n\nconst textDocument = (uri, text, version = 1) => ({\n  uri,\n  languageId: 'minilang',\n  version,\n  text,\n});\n\nconst itemsFrom = (response) => {\n  const result = response.result;\n  return Array.isArray(result) ? result : result.items;\n};\n\nconst positionOf = (text, line, needle, offset = 0) => {\n  const lines = text.split('\\\\n');\n  const character = lines[line].indexOf(needle);\n  assert.notEqual(character, -1, \"'`missing ${needle} on line ${line}`);\n  return { line, character: character + offset };\n};\n\nconst publishFrom = (server) => {\n  const publish = server\n    .takeNotifications()\n    .find((item) => item.method === '\"'textDocument/publishDiagnostics');\n  assert.ok(publish, 'expected textDocument/publishDiagnostics notification');\n  return publish.params;\n};\n\nconst asText = (value) => {\n  if (typeof value === 'string') return value;\n  if (\"'!value) return '\"'';\n  if (Array.isArray(value)) return value.map(asText).join('\\\\n');\n  if (typeof value === 'object') {\n    if (typeof value.value === 'string') return value.value;\n    if (typeof value.kind === 'string' && typeof value.value === 'undefined') return JSON.stringify(value);\n  }\n  return JSON.stringify(value);\n};\n\nasync function runRule(name, fn) {\n  try {\n    await fn();\n    console.log(\"'`PASS ${name}`);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`FAIL ${name}: ${err.message}`);\n    throw err;\n  }\n}\n\n(async () => {\n  await runRule('\"'R1 transport framing', async () => {\n    const message = { jsonrpc: '2.0', id: 7, result: { ok: true } };\n    const framed = encodeMessage(message);\n    const body = JSON.stringify(message);\n\n    assert.match(framed, /\"'^Content-Length: '\"\\\\d+\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n/);\n    const headerEnd = framed.indexOf('\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n');\n    assert.ok(headerEnd >= 0, 'missing CRLF separator');\n    const header = framed.slice(0, headerEnd);\n    const lengthMatch = header.match(/Content-Length:\\\\s*(\\\\d+)/);\n    assert.ok(lengthMatch, 'missing Content-Length header value');\n    assert.equal(Number(lengthMatch[1]), body.length);\n    assert.equal(framed.slice(headerEnd + 4), body);\n\n    const buffer = new MessageBuffer();\n    assert.deepEqual(buffer.push(framed.slice(0, 10)), []);\n    const firstRound = buffer.push(framed.slice(10));\n    assert.equal(firstRound.length, 1);\n    assert.deepEqual(firstRound[0], message);\n\n    const secondMessage = { jsonrpc: '2.0', id: 8, result: { ok: false } };\n    const batch = framed + encodeMessage(secondMessage);\n    const splitter = Math.floor(batch.length / 2);\n\n    const batchBuffer = new MessageBuffer();\n    const head = batchBuffer.push(batch.slice(0, splitter));\n    const tail = batchBuffer.push(batch.slice(splitter));\n    const all = [...head, ...tail];\n\n    assert.equal(all.length, 2);\n    assert.deepEqual(all[0], message);\n    assert.deepEqual(all[1], secondMessage);\n  });\n\n  await runRule('R2 lifecycle capabilities', async () => {\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n\n    const init = await server.handle(request('initialize', {}, 1));\n    assert.ok(init.result?.capabilities);\n    assert.equal(init.result.capabilities.textDocumentSync, 2);\n    assert.ok(init.result.capabilities.completionProvider);\n    assert.equal(init.result.capabilities.definitionProvider, true);\n    assert.equal(init.result.capabilities.hoverProvider, true);\n\n    const shutdown = await server.handle(request('shutdown', {}, 2));\n    assert.deepEqual(shutdown, {\n      jsonrpc: '2.0',\n      id: 2,\n      result: null,\n    });\n\n    assert.equal(await server.handle(notification('exit')), null);\n  });\n\n  await runRule('R3 diagnostics on didOpen include undefined and arity', async () => {\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n    const uri = 'file:///selftest-open.mini';\n    const text = [\n      'fn add(a, b) {',\n      '  return a',\n      '}',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  let answer = add(1)',\n      '  return missing',\n      '}',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didOpen', { textDocument: textDocument(uri, text) }));\n    const publish = publishFrom(server);\n    const diagnostics = publish.diagnostics;\n    assert.equal(publish.uri, uri);\n    assert.ok(Array.isArray(diagnostics));\n    assert.ok(diagnostics.length > 0);\n\n    const messages = asText(diagnostics.map((d) => d.message)).toLowerCase();\n    assert.match(messages, /undefined|not defined|undeclared/);\n    assert.match(messages, /arity|argument|expected/);\n    assert.equal(server.getDiagnostics(uri).length, diagnostics.length);\n  });\n\n  await runRule('R4 syntax recovery still returns semantic diagnostics', async () => {\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n    const uri = 'file:///selftest-syntax.mini';\n    const text = [\n      'fn add(a, b) {',\n      '  return a + b',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  let answer = add(1)',\n      '  return missing',\n      '',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didOpen', { textDocument: textDocument(uri, text) }));\n    const publish = publishFrom(server);\n    const diagnostics = publish.diagnostics;\n    assert.ok(diagnostics.length > 0);\n\n    const messages = asText(diagnostics.map((d) => d.message)).toLowerCase();\n    assert.match(messages, /undefined|not defined|undeclared/);\n    assert.match(messages, /arity|argument|expected/);\n    assert.equal(server.getDiagnostics(uri).length, diagnostics.length);\n  });\n\n  await runRule('R5 didChange updates and clears stale diagnostics', async () => {\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n    const uri = 'file:///selftest-change.mini';\n    const withErrors = [\n      'fn add(a, b) {',\n      '  return a + b',\n      '}',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  return missing',\n      '}',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n    const fixed = [\n      'fn add(a, b) {',\n      '  return a + b',\n      '}',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  return add(1, 2)',\n      '}',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didOpen', { textDocument: textDocument(uri, withErrors, 1) }));\n    const first = publishFrom(server);\n    assert.ok(first.diagnostics.length > 0, 'expected initial diagnostics for stale-state setup');\n\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didChange', {\n      textDocument: { uri, version: 2 },\n      contentChanges: [{ text: fixed }],\n    }));\n\n    const second = publishFrom(server);\n    const fixedMessages = asText(second.diagnostics.map((d) => d.message)).toLowerCase();\n    assert.equal(second.uri, uri);\n    assert.ok(second.diagnostics.length < first.diagnostics.length);\n    assert.equal(server.getDiagnostics(uri).length, second.diagnostics.length);\n    assert.equal(server.getDiagnostics(uri).length, second.diagnostics.length);\n    assert.ok(\"'!/missing|undefined|arity|argument/i.test(fixedMessages));\n  });\n\n  await runRule('\"'R6 completion filters by prefix and scope and exposes signatures', async () => {\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n    const uri = 'file:///selftest-completion.mini';\n    const text = [\n      'fn add(a, b) {',\n      '  return a + b',\n      '}',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  let localOnly = 1',\n      '  ad',\n      '}',\n      'fn other() {',\n      '  lo',\n      '}',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didOpen', { textDocument: textDocument(uri, text) }));\n\n    const scopedPrefix = itemsFrom(\n      await server.handle(request('textDocument/completion', {\n        textDocument: uri,\n        position: positionOf(text, 5, 'ad', 0),\n      }, 3)),\n    );\n    assert.ok(Array.isArray(scopedPrefix), 'completion result should be list');\n    const addItem = scopedPrefix.find((item) =>\n      typeof item.label === 'string' && (item.label.startsWith('add') || item.label.includes('fn add')),\n    );\n    assert.ok(addItem, 'completion should return add symbol for prefix ad');\n    assert.ok(\n      scopedPrefix.every((item) =>\n        typeof item.label \"'!== '\"'string' ||\n        item.label.toLowerCase() === 'let' ||\n        item.label.startsWith('ad') ||\n        item.label.startsWith('a') ||\n        item.label === 'fn'\n      ),\n      'completion should filter items to current prefix where applicable',\n    );\n\n    const signatureText = asText(addItem.label + ' ' + addItem.detail + ' ' + addItem.insertText + ' ' + addItem.documentation);\n    assert.match(signatureText, /add\\\\s*\\\\(\\\\s*a\\\\s*,\\\\s*b\\\\s*\\\\)/);\n\n    const scopeIsolation = itemsFrom(\n      await server.handle(request('textDocument/completion', {\n        textDocument: uri,\n        position: positionOf(text, 8, 'lo', 0),\n      }, 4)),\n    );\n    assert.ok(Array.isArray(scopeIsolation), 'completion result should be list');\n    assert.ok(\n      \"'!scopeIsolation.some((item) => typeof item.label === '\"'string' && item.label === 'localOnly'),\n      'completion in other scope should not suggest main-local symbol localOnly',\n    );\n  });\n\n  await runRule('R7 definition local-over-global and hover function info', async () => {\n    const uri = 'file:///selftest-def-hover.mini';\n    const text = [\n      'fn inc(value) {',\n      '  return value',\n      '}',\n      'fn main() {',\n      '  let inc = 99',\n      '  return inc',\n      '}',\n    ].join('\\\\n');\n\n    const server = new MiniLangServer();\n    await server.handle(notification('textDocument/didOpen', { textDocument: textDocument(uri, text) }));\n\n    const definition = await server.handle(request('textDocument/definition', {\n      textDocument: uri,\n      position: positionOf(text, 5, 'inc', 1),\n    }, 4));\n\n    const target = Array.isArray(definition.result)\n      ? definition.result[0]\n      : definition.result;\n    assert.ok(target && target.uri === uri, 'definition should resolve inside same file');\n    assert.equal(target.range.start.line, 4);\n\n    const hover = await server.handle(request('textDocument/hover', {\n      textDocument: uri,\n      position: positionOf(text, 5, 'inc', 1),\n    }, 5));\n\n    const hoverText = asText(hover.result?.contents || '').toLowerCase();\n    assert.match(hoverText, /fn\\\\s+inc\\\\(value\\\\)/);\n  });\n})();\nEOF\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
